name: Skolly! Skull holly berries on leaves.
description: A gothic festive delight of holly leaves adorned with skull berries. A cute christmas decoration to highlight the mantle piece. These little handcrafted beauties could make a nice stocking filler or place setting. They come as a pair and are each approx. 5inches in length.

name: Gus
description:
Gus is a larger scale ceramic skull, based on the Mexican Day of the Dead (Length 19cm, width 13cm & Height 12cm). He is handcrafted and one of a kind. He comes complete with an LED tea light, which brings his smiling face to life at dusk. 
If you would like to see more images please visit my blog at http://madamemunki.blogspot.com/

name: Lolita
description:
Lolita is a handbuilt, ceramic sculpture, based on Mexican Day of the Dead. She is one of a kind, with wings, painted flower and heart decoration, as well as a relief flower detail on the rear. She is a cheeky vintage belle, who can be illuminated after dusk with an LED tea light.
For more images please visit my Blog at http://madamemunki.blogspot.com/

name: Flora
description: Flora is a hand-crafted, one of a kind, ceramic skull sculpture, based on the Mexican Day of the Dead. This sculpture is coil constructed, fired and hand painted.
